reviewer_texts.Reference Validity:
Major reference-validity gaps remain. The biggest is a model mismatch: the cited Cantini/IMRN material treats **species-dependent** inhomogeneous TASEP rates \(r_{i,j}=x_i-y_j\), while the proof’s generator uses **site-dependent** stochastic-\(R\) rates \(r_i(a,b)=\frac{x_i-x_{i+1}}{x_i-tx_{i+1}}\) (and \(t\)-scaled reverse swap). That breaks the citation chain unless an explicit equivalence source is added.

